main event: A civilian reported seeing bright objects in the sky over Rockville, Maryland, on February 25, 1965, which were concluded by the Air Force to likely be birds.
interesting points: The sighting lasted about 25 minutes and included intermittent storm clouds obscuring the view., The objects appeared to progress through the sky at high speeds, estimated to be as fast as or faster than a plane., The objects were described as white and round., The Air Force determined that the objects did not display unusual shapes or motions., Approximately 6 to 8 objects were estimated to have been observed during the sighting.
witness description: female, 52 years old, reported the sighting directly to the USAF
